  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Pierce your <strong>red potato[es]</strong> with a fork, then add them to a plate and cook in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 10-12 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1689940685347-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1689940685347-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1689940685347-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1689940685347-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1689940685347-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potato is in the microwave, chop your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa</strong> to a pot with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and cook over a medium-high heat for 4-5 min or until the fish is starting to cooked through</p><p>Strain the fish, reserving the pot and the <strong>poaching milk</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1689940690126-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1689940690126-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1689940690126-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1689940690126-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1689940690126-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong>, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1689940694842-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1689940694842-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1689940694842-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1689940694842-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1689940694842-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potato is cooked through, carefully slice in half (it will be very hot!) and scoop the <strong>potato flesh</strong> out into a bowl, leaving a little around the edges of the skin</p><p>Combine the <strong>potato flesh</strong> with your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash it all together – this is your <strong>creamy mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1689940699042-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1689940699042-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1689940699042-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1689940699042-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1689940699042-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk your <strong>reserved poaching milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Add the <strong>poached basa</strong> and <strong>chopped parsley</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and gently stir until fully coated – this is your <strong>fish pie filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1689940720629-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1689940720629-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1689940720629-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1689940720629-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1689940720629-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>potato skins</strong> to a baking tray and divide the <strong>fish pie filling</strong> between them, then top with the <strong>creamy mash</strong> and the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until golden brown and the fish is cooked through – these are your <strong>fish pie loaded jacket potatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1689940723412-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1689940723412-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1689940723412-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1689940723412-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1689940723412-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sliced leek</strong> to the middle of a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and mix everything together</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the leek to form a sealed parcel[s] and add it to a separate baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the leek has softened</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1689940725790-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1689940725790-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1689940725790-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1689940725790-x1000.jpg",
